Enum - own datatype with specified values
enum myColor {red,blue,Yellow};
the compiler treats enum values a s 0,1,2 etc.
enum direction {up,down,left=10,right);
here up =0,down=1,left=10 and right=11

Char: anything in single quotes from character to numbers .can be signed/unsigned
char broiled = 'T' // this is char value
char broiled = T// T is a variable -wrong
char broiled ="T"// string - wrong
Char broiled = 65//is alright -right will consider ascii equivlaent

Escape sequences:
\a - Alert,\b= backspace,\f - formfeed,\n- newline,etc...

format specifiers:

